The paper focuses on using deep learning techniques for scene understanding in robotics applications, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of regularization and semantic segmentation also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The application of the proposed algorithm to mobile robot captured images indicates a potential focus on robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the use of natural language processing techniques for semantic segmentation may suggest a connection to the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
